# Frontend Development Rules

## Stack
React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, TanStack Query, TanStack Virtual, axios, Zustand, react-router-dom, lucide-react, react-resizable-panels.

## Dev Server
```bash
cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev
```
Runs on `http://localhost:5173`, proxies `/api` and `/auth` to backend at `localhost:8000`.

## Key Components
- `Uploader` — drag-and-drop pcap file upload (accepts `.pcap`, `.pcapng`, `.cap`, including tcpdump rotated suffixes).
- `PacketList` — virtualized packet list with protocol filter, substring search box, and pagination controls.
- `PacketTree` — expandable protocol layer tree; clicking a layer highlights its bytes in `HexViewer`.
- `HexViewer` — hex/ASCII dump of selected packet with highlighted layer byte ranges.
- `StatsTabs` — protocol hierarchy, endpoints (Tx/Rx), conversations, IP/country statistics, IO graph (bucket/metric controls); endpoint rows can filter the packet list, while conversation rows expose explicit Session and Follow actions. `ConversationsView` supports a Group by IP pair toggle that aggregates multiple port-level flows between the same source/destination IPs; aggregate rows expand/collapse to child rows, child rows retain full port-level details, Session/Follow actions stay on flat or child rows only, and toggling grouping resets expanded groups. IP/country/session views render SVG flag icons from backend country codes, keep backend-provided `country_flag` as fallback data, and use the local-network icon for `LAN`; do not print native flag emoji directly because Windows may render regional-indicator letters instead of flags.
- `SessionView`, `SessionSequenceDiagram`, `SessionDataFlow` — modal session inspector launched from the Conversations table. Sequence mode requests up to 5000 packets at offset 0; data-flow mode paginates with detail panes powered by `getPacketDetail`. The header's Filter packets action jumps back to the main packet list with an exact TCP/UDP 5-tuple connection filter; do not use chat-oriented copy for this action. Pass both `country_code` and `country_flag` into `FlagIcon` whenever rendering `GeoInfo`.
- `FollowStream` — modal that reconstructs one TCP/UDP conversation's payload (ASCII or hex view), client vs server color-coded; truncation banner when the 1 MB/direction cap is hit.
- `CaptureCommandPanel` — dockable panel that hosts two modes (tabs): `CaptureCommandBuilder` (form-driven tcpdump/pktmon command with shell-escaped args + live preview + Copy) and `CaptureCommandAIGenerator` (natural-language → tcpdump/pktmon command via `/api/capture-command/generate` SSE; optional capture context). Panel keeps a shared `command` state but clears it on tab switch and at AI-generate start so a stale command can't be copied. Can pop out into a `FloatingWindow`.
- `AIChatPanel` and `ChatSessionSidebar` — persisted capture chat UI. The sidebar lists per-user sessions ordered by backend `updated_at`, supports resume/new-chat flows, and has selection mode for batch delete. When `AIChatPanel` creates a new thread, keep the local sidebar list fresh immediately instead of waiting for a long stream to finish.
- `HelpTooltip` — portal-based help popover for compact labels; hover is transient, while click/focus stays open until blur, Escape, or outside pointer. Keep viewport positioning clamped for narrow panes/floating windows.
- `FloatingWindow` — draggable floating window wrapper used to pop out the Capture Command panel.

## Pages
- `Login` — probes `/auth/me` on mount; GitHub OAuth redirect via `/auth/github/login`; shows `auth_error=not_allowed` when a GitHub login is not in the allowlist and preserves relative deep links including query strings.
- `Dashboard` — upload area + captures list with status polling and delete confirmation. `super_admin` users see an Admin button and can toggle `all=true` capture listing with optional owner filtering.
- `Admin` — super-admin-only page at `/admin` for allowed GitHub user CRUD, role changes, seed-admin display, and login status.
- `Capture` — 3-pane inspector with view mode toggle (Packets / Statistics), protocol dropdown, substring search, CSV/JSON export buttons, Session and Follow Stream launch from conversation rows, session-to-packet-list connection filtering by exact TCP/UDP 5-tuple, multi-select packets (click / ctrl-click / shift-range) with an "Explain selected packets" bar (one-shot `/explain` SSE), and a right-side Capture Command dock (toggle + pop-out via `FloatingWindow`). AI chat is reached via the Dashboard threads, not a Capture view mode.

## Internationalization
- `react-i18next` is initialized from `src/i18n/i18n.ts`; translations live under `src/i18n/locales/{en,zh}/translation.json`.
- `useLanguageStore` persists `pcapgo-language` and calls `i18n.changeLanguage`; language selectors exist on Login, Dashboard, and Capture so logged-out users can switch before OAuth.
- User-facing copy in components/pages should use `t(...)` unless it is protocol text, a file extension, command syntax, or another intentional literal.

## API Client
- `frontend/src/api/client.ts` exports an axios instance (`baseURL: "/"`, `withCredentials: true`) and typed helpers for all backend endpoints.
- The axios interceptor hard-redirects to `/login` on 401 unless already on `/login`.
- Admin helpers are `listAllowedUsers`, `addAllowedUser`, `removeAllowedUser`, and `updateAllowedUserRole`; capture listing accepts `{ all?: boolean; owner?: string }`.
- Chat helpers include thread list/create/get/delete, `batchDeleteChatThreads`, and streaming messages. Chat streaming uses `fetch` + a `ReadableStream` reader (not `EventSource`, which can't POST) so the caller can pass an `AbortSignal` for the Stop button; SSE frames are split on `\n\n` and `[DONE]` terminates the stream.
- `packetsExportUrl(...)` builds a direct browser-download URL (cookie auth rides along on the GET) honoring active `proto`/`q` filters.
- Pages use TanStack Query for data fetching, caching, and invalidation.

## State Management
- `useAuthStore` (Zustand) holds the current `User | null` and `loading` state.
- `useCaptureStore` (Zustand) holds the selected packet index, multi-select state (`selectedIndices`, `lastClickedIdx`), protocol filter, and optional exact 5-tuple `connectionFilter` used when jumping from Session View back to the main packet list.
- `useThemeStore` (Zustand) holds the active theme (`dark` | `light` | `obsidian`) and applies it to `document.documentElement` via `applyTheme` (sets `data-theme`).
- `useAIDockStore` (Zustand) tracks the Capture Command dock open/pop-out UI state.
- `src/hooks/` exists as an empty directory; place future custom hooks there, not in `lib/`.

## Auth Flow
- GitHub OAuth: redirect to `/auth/github/login`, callback at `/auth/github/callback`.
- JWT stored in `pcap_session` cookie (httpOnly, secure in production, SameSite=Lax).
- `/auth/me` returns current allowlisted user with `role` or 401. Removed allowlist users are redirected to login on the next protected request.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS with a theme system (`dark` | `light` | `obsidian`) driven by a `data-theme` attribute on `<html>`; `applyTheme` in `useThemeStore` sets it. Theme tokens are defined per-theme in `tailwind.config.js` / `src/index.css`.
- Color tokens are `panel-bg`, `panel-header`, `panel-border`, `panel-text`, `panel-muted`, `panel-accent`, `panel-success`, `panel-warning`, `panel-error`.
- Default font is a monospace stack (`JetBrains Mono`, `Fira Code`).
- Wireshark-style row colors are defined in `src/index.css` (`.tr-tcp`, `.tr-udp`, `.tr-icmp`, `.tr-selected`).
- `captureCommandBuilder.ts` shell-quotes free-text values (`shellQuote` / `shellQuoteIfNeeded`) so interface/file/path/BPF values with spaces or embedded quotes paste safely into a shell.

## Build
```bash
cd frontend && npm run build
```
Output to `frontend/dist/`. Served by nginx in the test compose or by FastAPI `StaticFiles` in standalone mode.

## Testing
```bash
cd frontend && npx vitest run              # Single run
cd frontend && npx vitest                  # Watch mode
cd frontend && npm run typecheck           # App TypeScript check
cd frontend && npm run typecheck:test      # Test TypeScript check
```

Tests live in `frontend/src/__tests__/`, organized by `components/`, `pages/`, `api/`, and `lib/`. 23 test files cover:
- **Components** (14): Uploader, PacketList, PacketTree, HexViewer, StatsTabs, ConversationsView, SessionView (including Filter packets callback), SessionSequenceDiagram, SessionDataFlow, FollowStream, CaptureCommandPanel, CaptureCommandBuilder, CaptureCommandAIGenerator, FloatingWindow
- **Pages** (4): Login, Dashboard, Admin, Capture (including connection-filter mode)
- **App router** (1): routing based on auth state
- **Pure logic** (2): API client (axios), Zustand stores (including connectionFilter), captureCommandBuilder (incl. shell-escaping)

`vitest` config in `vite.config.ts` uses `jsdom`, `globals: true`, and `setupFiles: ["./src/test-setup.ts"]`.
- `src/test-setup.ts` is the configured setup file and is shared with `src/__tests__/test-setup.ts`; use `@/` alias imports inside setup code so paths resolve from both locations.
- Source imports use the `@/` alias resolving to `frontend/src/`.
- Test files are excluded from the app TypeScript build (`tsconfig.json` and `tsconfig.app.json` exclude `src/__tests__` and `src/test-setup.ts`).
- `tsconfig.test.json` extends `tsconfig.app.json`, includes tests + setup, and adds `vitest/globals` and `@testing-library/jest-dom` types.
